<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Perfume1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pérfume</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Perfúme,</orth> subst. 1) sweet odour, fragrance: <bibl n="shak. son 104.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 104, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.302" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 302</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.217" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 217</bibl>.<lb />2) a substance emitting sweet odour: <bibl n="shak. son 130.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 130, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.225" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 225</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 13</bibl>. <cit><quote>their diseased --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 207</bibl></cit>, == perfumed mistresses.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>